query.result:
1 That sun that previously warmed my chest with love, 2 had revealed to me the beautiful truth, 3 testing and retesting, the sweet aspect;
4 and I, to confess myself correct and certain 5 as much as was appropriate 6 raised my head to speak more loftily;
7 but a vision appeared that held me 8 so tightly to itself, to see itself, 9 that I did not remember my confession.

10 As through transparent and clear glass, 11 or through limpid and tranquil waters, 12 not so deep that the bottom is lost,
13 the reflections of our faces return 14 so faint, that a pearl on a white forehead 15 does not strike our pupils less forcefully;
16 such I saw more faces ready to speak; 17 so that I fell into the opposite error 18 to that which kindled love between man and fountain.

